race.comment: NEVERMISTA (6) has become a perennial placegetter, finding the frame in all eight starts this campaign. Missed by a whisker last start at Gunnedah and only needs to hold his form to be right there again. BLUE DE BEERS (1) continues to attract market support. Has been gelded since being reeled in as favourite at Tamworth last month. Can improve sharply after the snip. INVINCIBLE PHANTOM (10) got off the mark in fine style when resuming and has followed it up with two solid efforts. Peaking now on the quick back-up as he steps back out to a winning trip. Genuine threat. BOLO MISS (3) was poised to strike when resuming at Cowra off 271 days but came up short. Wary of a flat 2UP run but is definitely worth including.
